<br>
Its up to your play style/what you want.<br>
<br>
Its all opinion really.<br>
<br>
My opinion?<br>
<br>
I like norse.  We get decent stats (so do dorfs who also get better inherent resists due to starting racial resists).  They only race I wouldnt consider, IMO, is kobold.  No real reason except I just dont like the skin.<br>
<br>
<br>
As far as Axe or Hammer?  Hmmmm....  Well I spent 41 levels hammer specced and have been axe since.  Hamme was the choice hands down previously.  Now its a questionable proposition.  Hammer has a sweet anytime style if you are just looking to mash keys.  Some say Lambast with Provoke back up is sweet but I dont want a bleed to break mezz in RvR; plus parry is real tough to pull off in RvR (especially as a skald).  Axe seems to have  a higher delay so you hit for a bit more.  Personally I prefer axe styles; lotsa nice positional options.  Also axe has sweet resist match ups; neutral or bonus vs many of our enemies armor types.<br>
